---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
---

<BlogLayout title="Singles - Page 3">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Oasis Singles</h1>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <article class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Some Might Say (1995)</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <img 
              src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/d2/Oasis_Some_Might_Say_UK_CD1.jpg" 
              alt="Some Might Say Single Cover"
              class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-md mb-4"
            />
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Single Statistics</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
              <li>Release Date: April 24, 1995</li>
              <li>UK Chart Position: #1</li>
              <li>Weeks on Chart: 15</li>
              <li>Sales: Over 300,000 copies (UK)</li>
              <li>Parent Album: (What's the Story) Morning Glory?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">B-Sides</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
              <li>Talk Tonight</li>
              <li>Acquiesce</li>
              <li>Headshrinker</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-4">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Historical Significance</h3>
              <p>Their first UK number one single and the last to feature original drummer Tony McCarroll.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Roll with It (1995)</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <img 
              src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c9/Oasis_Roll_with_It_UK_CD1.jpg" 
              alt="Roll with It Single Cover"
              class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-md mb-4"
            />
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Single Statistics</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
              <li>Release Date: August 14, 1995</li>
              <li>UK Chart Position: #2</li>
              <li>Weeks on Chart: 13</li>
              <li>Sales: Over 505,000 copies (UK)</li>
              <li>Parent Album: (What's the Story) Morning Glory?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">B-Sides</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
              <li>Rockin' Chair</li>
              <li>Live Forever (Live at Glastonbury '95)</li>
              <li>Step Out</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-4">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">The Battle of Britpop</h3>
              <p>Famous for its chart battle with Blur's "Country House" in what became known as "The Battle of Britpop".</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <div class="flex justify-between mt-8">
        <a href="/singles/2" class="inline-block bg-black text-white px-6 py-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-800">
          ‚Üê Previous Page
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>